SAA informed its more than 5,000 employees that it's restructuring. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - South African Airways (SAA) gave an update about the planned restructuring. SAA informed its more than 5,000 employees that it's restructuring. It is estimated that about 944 staff will be affected. The national carrier has had its fair share of financial turbulence. The airline has incurred over R28-billion in cumulative losses over the past 13 years.